source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1960, 1970, 1980, 1991, 2000, 2010 censuses; (b) adjusted for age heaping; (c) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (d) official estimates through 2023; (e) only total population for 1946 Census; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2022; (b) registered births classified by age of mother and the underlying female population by age through 2021; (c) birth-histories data from the 1999 FHS and 2011, 2015-2016 MICS; (d) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1970, 1991, 2000, 2010 censuses and 2006, 2011 MICS; (e) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1960, 1980, 1991, 2000 censuses and 2006, 2011, 2015-2016 MICS. In addition, the (a) registered births classified by age of mother and the underlying female population by age through 2000; (b) adjusted for underregistration; (c) birth-histories data from the 1991 FHS; (d) adjusted fertility using Brass P/F ratio method (or variants) with data on children ever born and births in the preceding 12 (or 24/36) months, both classified by age of mother, from the 1991 FHS; (e) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1958-2012 Education Stats and 1960, 1980 censuses have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) official estimates through 2010; (b) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2020; (c) adjusted for underreporting of infant and child deaths; (d) adult deaths adjusted for underregistration using death distribution methods; (e) mortality rates for older ages were adjusted; (f) estimates using HIV/AIDS model life tables and estimates of under-five mortality (5q0) and adult mortality (45q15) with UNAIDS estimates of adult HIV prevalence, and ART coverage for children and adults. Mortality rates for Spectrum were calculated by removing AIM's estimates of HIV-related mortality from all-cause mortality rate estimates published in the 2024 revision of the World Population Prospects.

source.Name: Age Mortality
source.Summary: Adult and Old Age Mortality: Estimates derived from: (a) deaths by age and sex available from Register through 2020; (b) adjusted for underregistration; (c) estimates of under-five, adult and old age mortality.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) official estimates of infant and child mortality through 2017; (b) registered infant and child deaths through 2023; (c) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 1991 FHS and 1996 MCMS; (d) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1999 FHS and 2000 Census and 2006, 2011 MICS; (e) International estimates used up to 2021. In addition, the direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 2015-2016 MICS have been considered.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination; (b) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (c) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
